PropertyOverride.Name: id
PropertyOverride.Description: The 'id' built-in railML property [readonly String] holds a globally unique identifier. It is generated at object creation and never changed. Making object copies with ordinary CAD system commands or with RailCOMPLETE commands (such as RC-CopySelectionAlongPath) will assign a new globally unique id to each copy.

PropertyOverride.Name: TimeStamp
PropertyOverride.Description: The 'TimeStamp' built-in property [readonly ComplexType] holds version history for the object, such as creation time, number of times modified, who modified it etc. The minimum time lapse between registered timestamps is defined in the DNA.

PropertyOverride.Name: RcType
PropertyOverride.Description: The 'RcType' built-in property [readonly Enum] holds the object type name as defined in the current Definition of Network Assets (DNA). Additional info may be given as DisplayName for each object.

PropertyOverride.Name: Variant
PropertyOverride.Description: The 'Variant' built-in property [Enum] holds the currently selected Variant for the object. If the DNA object type declaration does not define any Variants, then the Variant property is void.

PropertyOverride.Name: code
PropertyOverride.Description: The 'code' built-in railML property typically holds an alphanumerical string which is suitable for machine interpretation, identfying the object in a limited context. E.g., a point machine could derive its code (e.g.: '501_3') from its position within a switch ('3') and the switch's own code ('501'). The same code may appear several times within one model, but in different contexts (e.g.: different stations).

PropertyOverride.Name: name
PropertyOverride.Description: The 'name' built-in railML property typically holds a more ornamented version of the object's code, making it suitable for human reading but not for further parsing. Example: 'Drv.501_3' ('point drive machine 501.3'). Most objects will show their 'name' property as a text element in the CAD drawing, along with the symbol's 2D graphics. Hide/unhide text in the drawing using the ShowLayer tool.

PropertyOverride.Name: Stage
PropertyOverride.Description: The 'Stage' built-in property holds a free-format string encoding the object's placement in the succession of construction stages for your project. Hint: Append '_stage2000-6000' etc to your object layer names and assign a formula: Stage = layer:sub(-9).

PropertyOverride.Name: lang
PropertyOverride.Description: The 'lang' (language) built-in railML property shall not be available to this railway administration.

PropertyOverride.Name: dir
PropertyOverride.Description: The 'dir' built-in railML enum property [up, down, both, none, unknown] holds the basic orientation of a point object.

PropertyOverride.Name: Alignment
PropertyOverride.Description: The 'Alignment' built-in property [Reference] refers to the alignment that the object belongs to, also referred to as its 'own alignment'. The point object's mileage property is the mileage found perpendicularly to this own alignment.

PropertyOverride.Name: ReferenceAlignment
PropertyOverride.Description: The 'ReferenceAlignment' built-in property [Reference] refers to the alignment that the object's own alignment has appointed as it's 'parent' (reference) (at the point object's current location). See the Alignment Manager tools's tab named 'Reference'. The point object's referenceMileage property is the mileage found perpendicularly to this reference alignment.

PropertyOverride.Name: geoCoord
PropertyOverride.Description: The 'geoCoord' built-in railML property [Triplet {X,Y,Z}] holds the 'real' position, expressed in World coordinates. This triplet is the basis for all geometrical computations involving the point object.

PropertyOverride.Name: Seq
PropertyOverride.Description: The 'Seq' built-in property [Integer] is a freely usable integer. It is typically used as a running number when it is convenient to put a formula to the code property, e.g.: code = 'Xyzzy-'..seq*2. Hint: Use the Object Manager's 'Fill series' to generate a Seq sequence n, n+1, n+2n....

PropertyOverride.Name: LuaExpressions
PropertyOverride.Description: The 'LuaExpressions' built-in property [Collection] gives , to all formulas stored in the object.

PropertyOverride.Name: description
PropertyOverride.Description: The 'description' built-in railML property is typically void or holds a short text with procurement or construction instructions. Typically, such descriptions will be included in tender documents.

PropertyOverride.Name: SymbolFrame
PropertyOverride.Description: The 'SymbolFrame' built-in property defines a symbol frame to be shown around the 2D symbol in the CAD drawing, such as a 'Warning' or 'Error' frame. Available symbol frames are declared in the administration's Style Definitions file. Many symbol frames can be toggled on/off using the RC-ShowLayer tool.

PropertyOverride.Name: Color
PropertyOverride.Description: The 'Color' CAD system property defines the object's color (i.e., only graphics drawn on layer 0 in the object's block definition). If this property is 'ByLayer' then color is inherited from the layer that the objectbelongs to.

PropertyOverride.Name: Layer
PropertyOverride.Description: The 'Layer' CAD system property defines the layer that the object belongs to. Edit layers using the CAD system's layer manager tool.

PropertyOverride.Name: Linetype
PropertyOverride.Description: The 'Linetype' CAD system property defines the linetype that the object is drawn with, usually a continuous or a dashed pattern.

PropertyOverride.Name: Lineweight
PropertyOverride.Description: The 'Lineweigth' CAD system property defines the line width when plotting to paper or PDF, unless the CAD system's color table mechanisms are exploited instead.

PropertyOverride.Name: GlobalWidth
PropertyOverride.Description: The 'GlobalWidth' CAD system property defines a global width for polyline objects, used to distinguish alignment types visually in modelspace.

PropertyOverride.Name: TargetAlignment
PropertyOverride.Description: The 'TargetAlignment' built-in property [Reference] holds an object reference to the alignment that branches out from a continued track at a stock rail joint.

PropertyOverride.Name: SwitchGeometry
PropertyOverride.Description: The 'Switch Geometry' built-in property [left | right] defines which switch leg has the lowest radius.

PropertyOverride.Name: ConnectionCourse
PropertyOverride.Description: The 'Connection course' built-in property [left | right] defines which switch leg is associated with the branching alignment. Note: Switch geometry and connection course may be different.

PropertyOverride.Name: ContinuingWithBegin
PropertyOverride.Description: The 'ContinuingWithBegin' built-in property [True | False] is True iff the TargetAlignment's start is close the continuation.

PropertyOverride.Name: ExtendingFromEnd
PropertyOverride.Description: The 'ExtendingFromEnd' built-in property [True | False] is True iff own Alignment's end is close the continuation.

PropertyOverride.Name: model
PropertyOverride.Description: The 'model' built-in railML property specifies the object's model (general model info). Use the various metadata entries for storing specific model information.

PropertyOverride.Name: kind
PropertyOverride.Description: The 'kind' built-in railML property [blockDerail | singleCatchPoints | doubleCatchPoints] identifies the kind of derailer.

PropertyOverride.Name: derailSide
PropertyOverride.Description: The 'derailSide' built-in railML property [left | right] denotes the side of the track that a derailing train will take.

LuaFunction.Name: _FE_DIV_text()
LuaFunction.Description: Returns a text to be displayed inside the Watch symbol's frame. The text consists of the code from each visible object related with 'Is watch for anything'.
LuaFunction.Formula: function _FE_DIV_text() local r,n,t,i r,n = RC__getCollectionOfRelatedObjects("Is watch for anything") if n == 0 then t = "?" else t = r[0].code for i = 1,n-1 do t = t..", "..r[i].code end end return t end

LuaFunction.Name: _FE_DIV_marker_name()
LuaFunction.Description: Obtains marker's name, a list of 'code' for all objects related to this marker with 'Er markør for anything'.
LuaFunction.Formula: function _FE_DIV_marker_name(obj) if obj == nil then obj = this end local RelationName = "Er markør for anything" local r,n = RC__getCollectionOfRelatedObjects(RelationName) if n == 0 then return "UNFINISHED - Relate with '"..RelationName.."'." else local s,i s = "("..r[0].code for i = 1, n-1 do s = s..", "..r[i].code end return s..")" end end

LuaFunction.Name: _FE_DIV_sporbrukgrense_name()
LuaFunction.Description: Obtains the name of a track usage delimiter element, inherited from the two surrounding track usage section elements.
LuaFunction.Formula: function _FE_DIV_sporbrukgrense_name() first = DownSections.Count == 0 and "-" or DownSections[0].Code second = UpSections.Count == 0 and "-" or UpSections[0].Code if (MileageIncreasesTowardsLeft == 'True') then first,second = second,first end return "(" .. first .. "/" .. second .. ")" end

LuaFunction.Name: _FE_DIV_sporbrukgrense_objectInfo()
LuaFunction.Description: Obtains the 'ObjectInfo' text for the track usage delimiter element.
LuaFunction.Formula: function _FE_DIV_sporbrukgrense_objectInfo() first = DownSections.Count == 0 and "-" or DownSections[0].Variant second = UpSections.Count == 0 and "-" or UpSections[0].Variant if (MileageIncreasesTowardsLeft == 'True') then first,second = second,first end return "Sporbruk: " .. first .. "/" .. second end

LuaExpression.Formula: if Variant == 'Signal 101-5 ID-skilt for dvergsignal og togsporsignal, 1-linje, 180x100' then return "R"..code elseif Variant == 'Signal 101-6 ID-skilt for dvergsignal, 1-linje, 300x100' then return "R"..code elseif Variant == 'Signal 101-7 ID-skilt for Veisignal, 200x300' then return "W"..code elseif Variant == 'Signal 101-8 ID-skilt for skiftesignal, 300x200' then return "Z"..code else return "Bad Variant ["..Variant.."]",_warning end

ColumnSpecification.Data:
if (alignment.type ~= "mainTrack" or alignment.mainDir == "down") and (dir == "up" or dir == "both") then pri = 2000 elseif (alignment.type ~= "mainTrack" or alignment.mainDir == "down") and (dir == "down" or dir == "both") then pri = 3000 elseif (alignment.type == "mainTrack" and alignment.mainDir == "up") and (dir == "up" or dir == "both") then pri = 0 elseif (alignment.type == "mainTrack" and alignment.mainDir == "up") and (dir == "down") then pri = 1000 else pri = -1,_warning end
local function is(pattern) if variant == nil then return false else return string.match(Variant,pattern) end end
--Signal prioritering if is("60") then delta = 0 elseif is("62") then delta = 1 elseif is("101") then delta = 2 elseif is("refleks") then delta = 3 elseif is("102") then delta = 4 elseif is("68C") then delta = 5 elseif is("72") then delta = 6
--Hastighetsskilt elseif is("68A") or is("68B") then delta = 7 elseif is("68F") then delta = 8 elseif is("68G") then delta = 9 elseif is("68D") then delta = 10 elseif is("69") then delta = 11
--Toglengdeskilt elseif is("74") then delta = this.prop("Train length") else delta = 40 end
return pri + delta

local a = Relations["Har balisegruppe"] if a.Count == 0 then return " " else if a[0].Variant == "Repeterbalisegruppe" then target=a[0].Relations["Henter ATC styringsinformasjon fra signal/sporveksel"][0]
elseif a[0].Variant == "Hastighetsbalisegruppe" then target=a[0].Relations["Har bremsekurve målpunkt i balisegruppe"][0].Relations["Har posisjonsdefinerende balise"][0] else target = a[0].Relations["Har posisjonsdefinerende balise"][0] end dif=target.ReferenceMileage-a[0].Relations["Har posisjonsdefinerende balise"][0].ReferenceMileage d = math.floor(dif + 0.5) if d == 0 then return " " else return math.abs(d) end end
ColumnSpecification.Title: Avstand merke [m]

ColumnSpecification.Data:
local a,d
if (Relations["Har balisegruppe"].Count == 0) then return " " else a = Relations["Har balisegruppe"][0].Relations["Har bremsekurve målpunkt i balisegruppe"] --Assume that start item has only one target item --First, find distance d = math.abs(a:distance()) if (d == 0) then return " " end --Second, find difference in elevation above sea level: t1 = getAlignmentInfo(this) t2 = getAlignmentInfo(a[0]) local e1 = t1.elevation local e2 = t2.elevation local g1 = t1.gradient local g2 = t2.gradient
if (tostring(dir) == "down") then g1 = -g1 g2 = -g2 elseif (tostring(dir) ~= "up") then return "*ERROR - bad direction*" end
local g3 = (e2 - e1) / d * 1000
-- Reduce info if gradients at each end are nearly identical to the average gradient: if (math.abs(g2-g1) < .01) and (math.abs(g3-g1) < .01) then if(g3 < 0) then return string.format("%.01f",-g3) end else if (g1 < 0) then return string.format("%.1f",-g1) end end end

local s0 = "" local s1 = "" local s5 = "" if variant ~= nil then s0 = variant else s0 = "" end if (attachment == nil) then s1 = "" s5 = "" else if getCollectionLength(Relations["Har balisegruppe"]) == 0 then
--TODO: Bruk heller Variant:match("64E") etc --TODO: Bruk heller getCollectionLength(Relations[Er stolpe for tellepunkt"] > 0 etc if string.find(Variant, "64E") ~= nil and Relations["Er stolpe for tellepunkt"] ~= nil and Relations["Er stolpe for tellepunkt"][0] ~= nil then s1= "
Tilhører 		"..Relations["Er stolpe for tellepunkt"][0].RcType
elseif (string.find(Variant, "68") ~= nil or string.find(Variant, "64E") ~= nil or string.find(Variant, "Signal 60") ~= nil) then obj= getNearbyPointObjects2D(15) s1= " " for i=0,obj.count-1 do if string.find(obj[i].variant, "balisegruppe") ~= nil or string.find(obj[i].RcType, "sporingsindikator") ~= nil then if obj[i].Relations["Har bremsekurve målpunkt i balisegruppe"] ~=nil then if obj[i].Relations["Har bremsekurve målpunkt i balisegruppe"].Count ~= 0 then s1 = "
Tilhører 		"..obj[i].name.." med målpunkt i balisegruppe "..obj[i].Relations["Har bremsekurve målpunkt i balisegruppe"][0].name break else s1="
Tilhører 		"..obj[i].name break end end elseif string.find(obj[i].RcType, "Telle") ~= nil and string.find(Variant, "64E") ~= nil then s1="
Tilhører 		"..obj[i].RcType break end end else s1 = " " end
if (string.find(Variant, "kryss") ~=nil) then obj= getNearbyPointObjects2D(10) s1= " " for i=0,obj.count-1 do if string.find(obj[i].RcType, "veksel")~=nil then s1="
Tilhører 		".."V."..tostring(obj[i].code) break elseif string.find(obj[i].RcType, "Drivmaskin")~=nil then Cd=tostring(obj[i].name) place=string.find(Cd,"%.") s1="
Tilhører 		".."V."..string.sub(Cd,1,place-1) break end end end
else if Relations["Har balisegruppe"][0].Relations["Har bremsekurve målpunkt i balisegruppe"] ~=nil then if Relations["Har balisegruppe"][0].Relations["Har bremsekurve målpunkt i balisegruppe"].Count ~= 0 then s1 = "
Tilhører 		"..Relations["Har balisegruppe"][0].name.." med målpunkt i balisegruppe "..Relations["Har balisegruppe"][0].Relations["Har bremsekurve målpunkt i balisegruppe"][0].name end else s1 = "
Tilhører 		"..Relations["Har balisegruppe"][0].name end end
if (attachment.variant == nil) then s5 = "" elseif string.find(Attachment.RcType, "SPB")~=nil then s5 = "
Montert på 		"..this.Attachment.Variant elseif string.find(Attachment.RcType, "SA%-SIG")~=nil then s5="
Montert på 		"..tostring(Attachment.name) else obj= getNearbyPointObjects2D(10) for i=0,obj.count-1 do if string.find(obj[i].RcType, "SA%-SIG")~=nil and (string.find(this.RcType, "Signal 68")~=nil)==false then s5="
Montert på 		"..tostring(obj[i].name) break elseif string.find(obj[i].RcType, "SPB")~=nil then s5="
Montert på 		"..tostring(obj[i].Variant) break else s5 = "
Montert på 		"..this.Attachment.Variant end end
end end return s0..s1..s5

ColumnSpecification.Data: -- Compare the X-coordinates (0 decimal degrees = East) for start and end of alignment in current User Coordinate System: o = DocumentData.Document.Database.Ucsorg u = DocumentData.Document.Database.Ucsxdir ang = math.atan2(u.y,u.x) p = RcAlignment.StartPoint u1x = (p.x-o.x)*math.cos(ang) + (p.y-o.y)*math.sin(ang) --u1y = -(p.x-o.x)*math.sin(ang) + (p.y-o.y)*math.cos(ang) p = RcAlignment.EndPoint u2x = (p.x-o.x)*math.cos(ang) + (p.y-o.y)*math.sin(ang) --u2y = -(p.x-o.x)*math.sin(ang) + (p.y-o.y)*math.cos(ang) return string.format("%s",u2x-u1x > 0 and "Right" or "Left")
x = RcAlignment.StartTangent.x y = RcAlignment.StartTangent.y z = RcAlignment.StartTangent.z g = 1000 * math.sqrt(z^2 / (x^2 + y^2)) return string.format("%.03f",g)
x = RcAlignment.EndTangent.x y = RcAlignment.EndTangent.y z = RcAlignment.EndTangent.z g = 1000 * math.sqrt(z^2 / (x^2 + y^2)) return string.format("%.03f",g)

ColumnSpecification.Data:
-- "Mastens stilling" betyr egentlig "mastesymbol med utligger". -- -- Nedenfor vil "*" bety enten O = gittermast, X = hengemast, 8 = bjelkemast G = GMB-mast -- -- *- Enkel utligger til høyre side i økende km-retning -- -* Enkel utligger til venstre side i økende km-retning -- *= Dobbel utligger til høyre side i økende km-retning -- =* Dobbel utligger til venstre side i økende km-retning -- -- Kombinasjoner er tillatt - enkel/dobbel til begge sider. --
local symbol = "*" if Variant:match("Henge") ~= nil then symbol = "X" elseif Variant:match("GMB") ~= nil then -- 2019-05-05 CLFEY foreslår 'G' for GMB-master. NB! Test på 'GMB' før 'B-mast' symbol = "G" elseif Variant:match("B-mast") ~= nil or Variant:match("H-mast") ~= nil then symbol = "O" elseif Variant:match("Bjelke") ~= nil then symbol = "8" else return "Ukjent Variant ["..Variant.."].",_warning
if (getCollectionLength(Relations["Er kl-mast for utligger"]) == 0) then return "Har ikke utligger",_warning elseif (getCollectionLength(Relations["Er kl-mast for utligger"]) == 1) then if (this.DistanceToAlignment - Relations["Er kl-mast for utligger"][0].DistanceToAlignment > 0) then return "-"..symbol else return symbol.."-" end else --getCollectionLength(Relations["Er kl-mast for utligger"]) > 1 return "Har ikke laget formel for multiple utliggere",_warning end

ColumnSpecification.Data: if (getAlignmentInfo().CurveType == "Straight") then return "Rettspor" elseif (getAlignmentInfo().CurveRotation:upper() == "CCW") then return "Venstrekurve" elseif (getAlignmentInfo().CurveRotation:upper() == "CW") then return "Høyrekurve" else return "Feil i kurverotasjon [" .. tostring(getAlignmentInfo().CurveRotation) .. "]",_warning end
ColumnSpecification.Title: Høyre / venstre kurve (Oslo i ryggen)

ColumnSpecification.Data: if (getAlignmentInfo().CurveType == "Straight") then return "Rettspor" else if (getAlignmentInfo().CurveRotation:upper() == "CCW") then if (LeftSided) then return "Innerkurve" else return "Ytterkurve" end else if (RightSided) then return "Innerkurve" else return "Ytterkurve" end end end
ColumnSpecification.Title: Innerkurve / ytterkurve

ColumnSpecification.Data: if (getAlignmentInfo().CurveType == "Straight") then return 0 else r = getAlignmentInfo().CurveRadius if (getAlignmentInfo().CurveRotation:upper() == "CW") then --clockwise if (RightSided) then --Innerkurve k = 81000/(2*r) else --Ytterkurve k = 63000/(2*r) end else --counterclockwise if (LeftSided) then --Innerkurve k = 81000/(2*r) else --Ytterkurve k = 63000/(2*r) end end return math.floor(k+0.5) end
ColumnSpecification.Title: Kurveutslag Ki / Ky [mm]

ColumnSpecification.Data: oh = math.floor(getAlignmentInfo().Cant + 0.5) if (RC__isNan(oh)) then return "(mangler overhøyde)" else return oh end
ColumnSpecification.Title: Overhøyde [mm]

ColumnSpecification.Data: oh35 = math.floor(getAlignmentInfo().Cant * (3500/1500) + 0.5) if (RC__isNan(oh35)) then return "(ukjent overhøyde)" else return oh35 end
ColumnSpecification.Title: Overhøyde- utslag i 3.5m høyde [mm]

ColumnSpecification.Data: local k,s,r if (getAlignmentInfo().CurveType == "Straight") then return 0 else oh35 = math.floor(getAlignmentInfo().Cant * (3500/1500) + 0.5) r = getAlignmentInfo().CurveRadius if (getAlignmentInfo().CurveRotation:upper() == "CW") then --clockwise if (RightSided) then --Innerkurve k = 81000/(2*r) s = 1.0 else --Ytterkurve k = 63000/(2*r) s = -1.0 end else --counterclockwise if (LeftSided) then --Innerkurve k = 81000/(2*r) s = 1.0 else --Ytterkurve k = 63000/(2*r) s = -1.0 end end if (RC__isNan(oh35)) then return "(mangler overhøyde)" else return math.floor(k + s*oh35 + .5) end end
ColumnSpecification.Title: Utslag mot signalet i 3.5m høyde [mm]

ColumnSpecification.Data: local k,s,r if (getAlignmentInfo().CurveType == "Straight") then return math.abs(DistanceToAlignment) else oh35 = math.floor(getAlignmentInfo().Cant * (3500/1500) + 0.5) r = getAlignmentInfo().CurveRadius if (getAlignmentInfo().CurveRotation:upper() == "CW") then --clockwise if (RightSided) then --Innerkurve k = 81000/(2*r) s = 1 else --Ytterkurve k = 63000/(2*r) s = -1 end else --counterclockwise if (LeftSided) then --Innerkurve k = 81000/(2*r) s = 1 else --Ytterkurve k = 63000/(2*r) s = -1 end end if (RC__isNan(oh35)) then return "(mangler overhøyde)" else return math.abs(math.floor(100*(DistanceToAlignment + (k + s*oh35)/1000) + 0.5)/100) end end
ColumnSpecification.Title: Margin til stikningspunkt [m]

ColumnSpecification.Data: local s = "" local first = true if (prop("Hovedsignal") ~= "-") then s = prop("Hovedsignal") first = false end if (prop("Forsignal") == "Ja") then if (first) then s = "Fs" else s = s.."-Fs" end first = false end if (prop("Dvergsignal") == "Ja") then if (first) then s = "Ds" else s = s.."-Ds" end first = false end if (prop("Middelkontrollampe") == "Ja") then if (first) then s = "Mk" else s = s.."-Mk" end first = false end if (prop("Forsiktig kjøring") == "Ja") then if (first) then s = "FKs" else s = s.."-FKs" end first = false end if (prop("Hovedlinjesignal") == "Ja") then if (first) then s = "HLs" else s = s.."-HLs" end first = false end if (prop("Lysende hastighetssignal") == "Ja") then if (first) then s = "Hast" else s = s.."-Hast" end first = false end if (prop("Høyt skiftesignal") == "Ja") then if (first) then s = "Z" else s = s.."-Z" end first = false end return s
ColumnSpecification.Title: Bestykning

LuaFunction.Name: _KU_KFOE_Duct_getStartEndAndJump
LuaFunction.Description: Sampled formula. Returns alignmentInfo structs for one duct element's start and end, plus the jump length from start to end along the duct's alignment.
LuaFunction.Formula: function _KU_KFOE_Duct_getStartEndAndJump(AlignmentRefAndPos) --Interpret 'Cant' stored in duct's alignment as extra offset (usually the lift of the closest rail) [mm]: local id,pos,len2d,offset,s,e,a,b id = AlignmentRefAndPos.ref.id pos = AlignmentRefAndPos.pos len2d = getObjectFromId(id).RcAlignment.HorizontalProfile.Length offset = 0.499 * Model3DSeparation --pick samples at +/- offset from object's insertion point if pos < offset then a = 0 b = pos + offset elseif pos > len2d - offset then a = pos - offset b = len2d else a = pos - offset b = pos + offset end s = getAlignmentInfo(getAlignmentPos(id,a)) e = getAlignmentInfo(getAlignmentPos(id,b)) return s,e,b-a end

LuaFunction.Name: _KU_KFOE_Duct_Offset3dX
LuaFunction.Description: Sampled formula. Returns sideways offset for cable duct element (midway betwen end points on alignment).
LuaFunction.Formula: function _KU_KFOE_Duct_Offset3dX(AlignmentRefAndPos) local s,e,m s,e = _KU_KFOE_Duct_getStartEndAndJump(AlignmentRefAndPos) m = getAlignmentInfo(AlignmentRefAndPos.ref.id,(s.Point.X + e.Point.X)/2,(s.Point.Y + e.Point.Y)/2) return m.DistanceToAlignment end

LuaFunction.Name: _KU_KFOE_Duct_Offset3dZ
LuaFunction.Description: Sampled formula. Returns an extra elevation for the cable duct element, as stored in millimeter as Cant data. Copy cant data from closest track's relevant cant using Alignment Manager datagrid/Cant.
LuaFunction.Formula: function _KU_KFOE_Duct_Offset3dZ(AlignmentRefAndPos) local s,e,m s,e = _KU_KFOE_Duct_getStartEndAndJump(AlignmentRefAndPos) m = getAlignmentInfo(AlignmentRefAndPos) return (s.Elevation + e.Elevation)/2 + (s.Cant/1000 + e.Cant/1000)/2 - m.Point.Z end

LuaFunction.Name: _KU_KFOE_Duct_Rotation3dX
LuaFunction.Description: Sampled formula. Returns the pitch [Decimal Degrees] for the cable duct element, adding the effects of general vertical profile and the additional duct elevation stored as alignment cant.
LuaFunction.Formula: function _KU_KFOE_Duct_Rotation3dX(AlignmentRefAndPos) local s,e,m local jump s,e,jump = _KU_KFOE_Duct_getStartEndAndJump(AlignmentRefAndPos) sc = RC__isNan(s.Cant) and 0 or s.Cant ec = RC__isNan(e.Cant) and 0 or e.Cant return math.atan2((e.Elevation-s.Elevation) + (ec/1000-sc/1000),jump) * (180/math.pi) end

LuaFunction.Name: _KU_KFOE_Duct_Rotation3dZ
LuaFunction.Description: Sampled formula. Returns the pitch [Decimal Degrees] for the cable duct element, adding the effects of general vertical profile and the additional duct elevation stored as alignment cant.

LuaFunction.Name: _KU_KFOE_Duct_Linetype
LuaFunction.Description: Returns the CAD system 2D presentation line type for the cable duct, based on its Variant.
LuaFunction.Formula: function _KU_KFOE_Duct_Linetype() if Variant:match("1%-løps") then return "RC-DASHED-01" elseif Variant:match("2%-løps") then return "RC-DASHED-02" elseif Variant:match("3%-løps") then return "RC-DASHED-03" else return "Continuous",_info("Variant ["..Variant.."] has not been anticipated yet.") end end

LuaFunction.Name: _KU_KFOE_Duct_GlobalWidth
LuaFunction.Description: Returns the global width of the cable duct's 2D representation as a wide polyline.
LuaFunction.Formula: function _KU_KFOE_Duct_GlobalWidth() if Variant:match("1%-løps, 30 cm") then return 0.30 elseif Variant:match("1%-løps, 40 cm") then return 0.40 elseif Variant:match("2%-løps, 60 cm") then return 0.62 elseif Variant:match("3%-løps, 60 cm") then return 0.62 else return 0,_info("Variant ["..Variant.."] has not been anticipated yet.") end end

LuaFunction.Name: _KU_KFOE_Duct_Model3DName()
LuaFunction.Description: Returns the cable duct default 3D object model name.
LuaFunction.Formula: function _KU_KFOE_Duct_Model3DName() t = Sweep3D and "NO-BN-SWEEP-KU-KFØ-CABLEDUCT-" or "NO-BN-3D-KU-KFØ-CABLEDUCT-" if Variant == "Kabelkanal, betong, 1-løps, 30 cm" then return t.."300x1000-1-CHANNEL-WITH-50-50-COVER" elseif Variant == "Kabelkanal, betong, 1-løps, 40 cm" then return t.."400x1000-1-CHANNEL-WITH-50-50-COVER" elseif Variant == "Kabelkanal, betong, 2-løps, 60 cm" then return t.."620x2400-2-CHANNEL-WITH-70-70-COVER" elseif Variant == "Kabelkanal, betong, 3-løps, 60 cm" then return t.."620x2400-3-CHANNEL-WITH-70-70-COVER" else return "",_info("Variant ["..Variant.."] has not been anticipated yet.") end end

LuaFunction.Name: _KU_KFOE_duct_Model3DSeparation()
LuaFunction.Description: Returns the distance to the next 3D model insertion point along the alignment axis during 3D Preview or 3D Export. Must be called with '_position' as input argument.
LuaFunction.Formula: function _KU_KFOE_duct_Model3DSeparation(pos) -- TODO: A more elaborate function would rely on the actual size for each inserted 3D Model, which may vary as a sampled function along the alignment. -- This simple formula assumes that the Model3D is constant along the alignment, decided by the Variant (which applies to the whole alignment's length) -- TODO: Implement 'SweepMode3D' which interprets the given 3D Model Name as a 2D section to be sweeped (or twisted, if Cant info is provided). if Variant == "Kabelkanal, betong, 1-løps, 30 cm" then f = 2400/1000 b = 0.3 elseif Variant == "Kabelkanal, betong, 1-løps, 40 cm" then f = 2400/1000 b = 0.4 elseif Variant == "Kabelkanal, betong, 2-løps, 60 cm" then f = 1 b = 0.6 elseif Variant == "Kabelkanal, betong, 3-løps, 60 cm" then f = 1 b = 0.6 else return 3.1416,_info("Variant ["..Variant.."] has not been anticipated yet - so we assume 3.1416m 3D Model Separation...") end r = getAlignmentInfo(pos).CurveRadius -- Empirical formula, to allow a small separation between concrete elements in the "outer curve", but assuming that it will be cut in the "inner curve". if r == nil or r > 100 then return 2.4 / f + .005 elseif r < (0.8 / b) then return (2.4 - b) / f else return (2.4 - 0.8/r) / f + .005 end end

LuaFunction.Name: _KU_KFOE_tube_Offset3dZ()
LuaFunction.Description: Returns the flexible tube Z offset along the geometry, relative to the duct bottom located at the start of the tube's alignment geometry.
LuaFunction.Formula:
function _KU_KFOE_tube_Offset3dZ(cursor) local P1 = RcAlignment.StartPoint local ducts = getClosestAlignments("KU-KFØ Kabelkanal",P1.X,P1.Y) if getCollectionLength(ducts) == 0 then return 0,_info("UNFINISHED - No cable duct found at flexible tube's geometry start point.") end local Zref = getAlignmentInfo(ducts[0].id,P1.X,P1.Y).Point.Z
local ini = 0.2 --Length of initial level part local c = 0.8 --Length of cosine part local h1 = 0.1 --Start at bottom duct level +h1, make a cosine bend down to bottom duct -h1 local r = 0.5 --After horizontal movement, bend up from Zref-h1 as a quarter-circle with radius r local h2 = 0.4 --Finally, rise another h2, close to the tube's end (at the object to feed) local d = 0.1 --Horizontal length of the last steep ascent
local L = RcAlignment.HorizontalProfile.Length --2D length of the tube's geometry local L1 = ini --Start cosine bend local L2 = L1+c --End of cosine, start horizontal part local L3 = L-d-r --Start of arc local L4 = L-d --End of arc, start of steep ascent if L < ini+c+r+d then return 0,_info("UNFINISHED - Tube geometry is too short to generate Z offset.") end
local p = cursor.pos --Our 'cursor' running along the geometry from 0 to L
if p < L1 then --horizontal return Zref + h1
elseif p < L2 then --cosine return Zref + h1*math.cos(math.pi*((p-L1)/c))
elseif p < L3 then --horizontal return Zref - h1
elseif p < L4 then --circular arc return Zref - h1 + r*(1 - math.sqrt(1 -((p-L3)/r)^2))
else return Zref - h1 + r + h2*(p-L4)/d end end

LuaFunction.Name: _KU_KFOE_manhole_DistanceToAlignment()
LuaFunction.Description: Returns manhole's default 3D object model name.
LuaFunction.Formula: function _KU_KFOE_manhole_DistanceToAlignment() local diameter = Variant:upper():match("Ø(%d+)") local length = Variant:upper():match("(%d+)X%d+") local depth = Variant:upper():match("%d+X(%d+)") local MinFreeProfile = 2.30 --Bane NOR TRV value local StdFreeProfile = 2.52 --Bane NOR TRV value local d a = getClosestAlignments("KU-KFØ Kabelkanal") if diameter ~= nil then --Should "touch" MinFreeProfile, insertion point = center manhole at Top-of-rail d = MinFreeProfile + diameter/2000 elseif length ~= nil and depth ~= nil then --Should "touch" MinFreeProfile, insertion point = midpoint long side towards track at Top-of-rail if dir == "both" then d = MinFreeProfile + 0 elseif dir == "none" then d = MinFreeProfile + depth/1000 elseif dir == "up" then d = MinFreeProfile + length/2000 elseif dir == "down" then d = MinFreeProfile + length/2000 else return 4e-4,_info("UNFINISHED - Unknown direction") end else return 4e-4,_info("Variant ["..Variant.."] has not been anticipated yet.") end return RightSided and d or -d,_info("Distance to alignment deduced from direction and from manhole dimensions.") end

LuaFunction.Name: _KU_KFOE_manhole_Model3DName()
LuaFunction.Description: Returns manhole's default 3D object model name.
LuaFunction.Formula: function _KU_KFOE_manhole_Model3DName() local diameter = Variant:upper():match("Ø(%d+)") local length = Variant:upper():match("(%d+)X%d+") local depth = Variant:upper():match("%d+X(%d+)") local numberOfOrifices = Variant:upper():match("(%d+)%-VEIS") if Variant:match("Ø%d+") then return "NO-BN-3D-KU-MANHOLE-Ø"..diameter.."-H"..ManholeHeight.."-WITH-COVER" elseif Variant:upper():match("%d+X%d+") then if numberOfOrifices == nil then return "NO-BN-3D-KU-MANHOLE-L"..length.."-D"..depth.."-H"..ManholeHeight.."-WITH-COVER" else return "NO-BN-3D-KU-MANHOLE-L"..length.."-D"..depth.."-H"..ManholeHeight.."-"..numberOfOrifices.."-WAY-WITH-COVER" end else return "NO-BN-3D-UKJENT",_info("Variant ["..Variant.."] has not been anticipated yet.") end end

LuaFunction.Name: _EH_FUN_strecherSpanner_code()
LuaFunction.Description: Returns the code for a catenary strecher or spanner foundation, copied from its strecher / spanner.
LuaFunction.Formula: function _EH_FUN_strecherSpanner_code() m1 = getNearbyPointObjects2D(1.0,"EH-BAR Bardun") m2 = getNearbyPointObjects2D(1.0,"EH-KLO Strever") n1 = getCollectionLength(m1) n2 = getCollectionLength(m2) if n1 + n2 == 0 then return _warning,"UNFINISHED - OCS stretcher/spanner foundation has no strecher/spanner yet. Place OCS strecher/spanner onto foundation and connect with 'Er kl-fundament for kl-mast'." elseif n1 + n2 >= 2 then return _warning,"UNFINISHED - OCS stretcher/spanner foundation has more than one strecher/spanner - remove or adjust stage settings using layer names." elseif n1 == 1 then return m1[0].code elseif n2 == 1 then return m2[0].code else return _warning,"UNFINISHED - Too many objects placed on strecher/spanner foundation - remove or adjust stage settings using layer names." end end

LuaFunction.Name: NOBN_trk_getContinuationCode()
LuaFunction.Description: Returns a formated string containing the code properties '[Code1] --- [Code2]' for the two tracks that meet in a track continuation.
LuaFunction.Formula: function NOBN_trk_getContinuationCode() local first,second if RcType ~= "KO-SPF Sporfortsettelse" then return _error,"Bad object type ["..RcType.."] - 'KO-SPF Sporfortsettelse' was expected" else first = Alignment if first == nil then return "Bad or missing alignment reference",_warning end second = prop("Continued Alignment") if second == nil then return "Bad or missing continuing alignment reference",_warning end if first.id == second.id then return _error,"Own alignment and continuing alignment cannot be the same ["..first.Code.."]" end if (MileageIncreasesTowardsLeft == 'True') then first,second = second,first end return "["..first.Code.."] --- ["..second.Code.."]" end end

LuaFunction.Name: _KO_SPV_crossingCode()
LuaFunction.Description: Returns a formated string containing the code properties '[Code1] -X- [Code2]' for the two tracks that meet in a track crossing.
LuaFunction.Formula: function _KO_SPV_crossingCode() local first,second if RcType ~= "KO-SPV Sporkryss" then return "Bad object type ["..RcType.."], 'KO-SPV Sporkryss' was expected" else first = Alignment if first == nil then return "Bad or missing alignment reference",_warning end second = TargetAlignment if second == nil then return "Bad or missing intersecting alignment reference",_warning end if first.id == second.id then return "Alignment and intersecting alignment cannot be the same ["..first.Code.."]" end if (MileageIncreasesTowardsLeft == 'True') then first,second = second,first end return "["..first.Code.."] -X- ["..second.Code.."]" end end

CustomAttribute.Description: The 'AngularOffset' custom property [DD] is added to the object's basic 3D orientation. CustomAttribute.Name: SwitchControlAndLocking
CustomAttribute.Description: The 'SwitchControlAndLocking' custom property [Rm | Rl | Rr | Rb | Pl | Pr | Pb | Pn | Hl | Hr | Hb | Hn] defines the switch control and locking type. The abbreviations mean: R='Remote controlled', P='Pushbutton, electrically operated', H='Hand operated (hand thrown)', m='Machine locked (using a point machine or clamping device, with end position detection)', l='Keylocked for left switch leg train movements', r='Keylocked for right switch leg train movements', b='Keylocked for both right and left switch leg train movements (one at a time)', n='Not interlocked'.

Value.Description: Remote controlled, keylocked for left switch leg train movements
Remote controlled, keylocked for right switch leg train movements
Remote controlled, keylocked for both right and left switch leg train movements
Pushbutton controlled, keylocked for left switch leg train movements (one at a time)
Pushbutton controlled, keylocked for right switch leg train movements
Pushbutton controlled, keylocked for both right and left switch leg train movements
Hand operated (hand thrown), keylocked for left switch leg train movements
Hand operated (hand thrown), keylocked for right switch leg train movements
Hand operated (hand thrown), keylocked for both right and left switch leg train movements (one at a time)

CustomAttribute.Name: SwitchElectrification

CustomAttribute.Description: Both alignments must be railway tracks.

CustomAttribute.Name: mc_Continuity
CustomAttribute.Description: The switch's stock rail joint must be located on its own alignment, the branching track shall start or end in the through track.

CustomAttribute.Name: mc_Tangent
CustomAttribute.Description: The tracks shall share the same tangent where they meet (i.e., XY-plane differentiability when turning out) .

CustomAttribute.Name: mc_Elevation
CustomAttribute.Description: The through track and the branch track shall share the same elevation at the stock rail joint (Z-coordinate).

CustomAttribute.Name: mc_Gradient
CustomAttribute.Description: The tracks shall share the same gradient (pitch) at the stock rail joint [o/oo].

CustomAttribute.Name: mc_Cant
CustomAttribute.Description: The tracks shall share the same cant (roll / superelevation) at the stock rail joint [mm].

LuaFunction.Name: _KO_SPV_switchCode()
LuaFunction.Description: Returns a formated string containing the code properties '[Code1] -X- [Code2]' for the two tracks that meet in a track crossing.
LuaFunction.Formula: function _KO_SPV_switchCode() local first,second if RcType ~= "KO-SPV Sporveksel" then return "Bad object type ["..RcType.."], 'KO-SPV Sporveksel' was expected" else first = Alignment if first == nil then return "Bad or missing alignment reference",_warning end second = TargetAlignment if second == nil then return "Bad or missing branching alignment reference",_warning end if first.id == second.id then return "Alignment and branching alignment cannot be the same ["..first.Code.."]" end return "["..Alignment.code.."] -> ["..TargetAlignment.code.."]" end end

LuaFunction.Name: _KO_SPV_trackContinueCourse()
LuaFunction.Description: Returns a string holding either 'left' or 'right'. At present, 3-way switches (allowed in railML) are not modeled in RailCOMPLETE, i.e. ConnectionCourse being 'straight' leads to an error message.
LuaFunction.Formula: function _KO_SPV_trackContinueCourse() if (ConnectionCourse == "right") then return "left" elseif (ConnectionCourse == "left") then return "right" elseif (ConnectionCourse == 'straight') then return "Cannot use 'straight' connection course in 2-way switch, use 'left' or 'right'",_warning else return "Bad connection course ["..ConnectionCourse.."]",_error end end

LuaFunction.Name: NOBN_trk_getMileageForNearestHorizontalVertex()
LuaFunction.Description: Analyzes local alignment geometry and cant and returns nearest vertex' mileage.
LuaFunction.Formula: function NOBN_trk_getMileageForNearestHorizontalVertex() alignmentInfo = getAlignmentInfo() nearest = alignmentInfo.NearestHorizontalVertex -- insert "RE,RB" if cant station is closest nearestCant = alignmentInfo.NearestCantVertex vertexMileage = nearest.Item1 ~= nil and nearest.Item1.EndMileage or nearest.Item2.StartMileage if nearestCant ~= null and math.abs(nearestCant.Mileage - alignmentInfo.Mileage) < math.abs(vertexMileage - alignmentInfo.Mileage) and math.abs(vertexMileage - alignmentInfo.Mileage) > 1 then return nearestCant.Mileage else if nearest.Item2 ~= null then return nearest.Item2.StartMileage end if nearest.Item1 ~= null then return nearest.Item1.EndMileage end return 0,error_info("Bad data for function NOBN_trk_getMileageForNearestHorizontalVertex().") end end

LuaFunction.Name: NOBN_trk_getVariantForNearestHorizontalVertex()
LuaFunction.Description: Analyzes local alignment geometry and cant and returns nearest vertex' Variant, i.e. type of geometric vertex/cant.
LuaFunction.Formula: function NOBN_trk_getVariantForNearestHorizontalVertex() -- XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX TODO CLFEY 2019-08-02 XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX alignmentInfo = getAlignmentInfo() nearest = alignmentInfo.NearestHorizontalVertex nearestCant = alignmentInfo.NearestCantVertex -- insert "RE,RB" if cant station is closest vertexMileage = nearest.Item1 ~= nil and nearest.Item1.EndMileage or nearest.Item2.StartMileage if nearestCant ~= null and math.abs(nearestCant.Mileage - alignmentInfo.Mileage) < math.abs(vertexMileage - alignmentInfo.Mileage) and math.abs(vertexMileage - alignmentInfo.Mileage) > 1 then if math.abs(nearestCant.GradientIn) > 0 and math.abs(nearestCant.GradientOut) > 0 then return "REB" elseif (nearestCant.GradientIn == nil or nearestCant.GradientIn == 0) and math.abs(nearestCant.GradientOut) > 0 then return "RB" elseif (nearestCant.GradientOut == nil or nearestCant.GradientOut == 0) and math.abs(nearestCant.GradientIn) > 0 then return "RE" end end if nearest == nil then return "" end if nearest.Item1 ~= null and nearest.Item1.Type == "Curve" then if nearest.Item2 == nil or nearest.Item2.Type == "Straight" then return "KP" end if nearest.Item2.Type == "Curve" then return "FKP" end end if nearest.Item2 ~= null and nearest.Item2.Type == "Curve" then if nearest.Item1 == nil or nearest.Item1.Type == "Straight" then return "KP" end end if nearest.Item1 ~= null and nearest.Item1.Type == "Clothoid" then if nearest.Item2 ~= null and nearest.Item2.Type == "Clothoid" then if nearest.Item1.RadiusStart < nearest.Item1.RadiusEnd then return "FOB" else return "FOE" end end if nearest.Item1.RadiusStart < nearest.Item1.RadiusEnd then return "OB" else return "OE" end end if nearest.Item2 ~= null and nearest.Item2.Type == "Clothoid" then if nearest.Item2.RadiusEnd < nearest.Item2.RadiusStart then return "OB" else return "OE" end end return "" end

LuaExpression.Name: code
LuaExpression.Formula:
alignmentInfo = getAlignmentInfo() segment = alignmentInfo.Segment
if segment.RadiusStart == math.huge then text1 = "RL" else text1 = "R" .. string.format("%.3f",segment.RadiusStart) end
if segment.RadiusEnd == math.huge then text2 = "RL" else text2 = "R" .. string.format("%.3f",segment.RadiusEnd) end
vector = alignmentInfo.Tangent TangentAngle2D = math.atan2(vector.Y,vector.Z) if (math.cos(getUcsAngle() - TangentAngle2D) < 0) then text = "<" .. text2 .. "-" .. text1 .. ">" else text = "<" .. text1 .. "-" .. text2 .. ">" end
return "L=" .. string.format("%.3f",getAlignmentInfo().Segment.Length) .. "\\P" .. text

LuaFunction.Name: _EH_KTL_Layer()
LuaFunction.Description: Obtains the CAD system layer name for the catenary wire, based on its Variant.
LuaFunction.Formula: function _EH_KTL_Layer() if Variant:match("ikke kjørbar") then return "JBTKL_EH_KTL_Kontaktledning_Ikke_kjørbar" else return "JBTKL_EH_KTL_Kontaktledning_Kjørbar" end end

LuaFunction.Name: _EH_KTL_Linetype()
LuaFunction.Description: Obtains the CAD system linetype (continuous / dashed) for the catenary wire, based on its Variant.
LuaFunction.Formula: function _EH_KTL_Linetype() if Variant:match("ikke kjørbar") then return "RC-DASHED" else return "Continuous" end end

LuaFunction.Name: _EH_KTL_Color()
LuaFunction.Description: Obtains the CAD system color for the catenary wire, based on its Variant. If your CAD system uses a color table translator, then colors may indirectly control line color and width in print.
LuaFunction.Formula: function _EH_KTL_Color() if Variant:match("Sort") then return "White" elseif Variant:match("Blå") then return "30,144,255" elseif Variant:match("Lilla") then return "148,0,211" elseif Variant:match("Rød") then return "252,10,28" elseif Variant:match("Brun") then return "139,69,19" elseif Variant:match("Oransje") then return "255,140,0" elseif Variant:match("Grønn") then return "50,205,50" end end

LuaFunction.Name: _EH_KTL_Lineweight()
LuaFunction.Description: Obtains the CAD system lineweight (line width in print) for the catenary wire, based on its Variant.
LuaFunction.Formula: --AutoCAD needs lineweights to be of the form "x.yy mm": function _EH_KTL_Lineweight() if Variant:match("Sort") then return "0.35 mm" else return "0.40 mm" end end

LuaFunction.Name: _EH_KLO_code()
LuaFunction.Description: Obtains the code for the OCS catenary wire supsension system component, inherited from the associated contact wire, through the 'Er oppheng for kontaktledning' relation.
LuaFunction.Formula: function _EH_KLO_code() r = Relations["Er oppheng for kontaktledning"]:filter(function (x) return x.visible end) if getCollectionLength(r) == 0 then return "UNFINISHED - Relate OCS suspension wires with 'Er oppheng for kontaktledning' to its contact wire.",notice else return r[0].code end end

LuaFunction.Name: _EH_KLO_name()
LuaFunction.Description: Obtains the name for the OCS catenary wire suspension system component, from its 'code'.
LuaFunction.Formula: function _EH_KLO_name() --Assume that each wire part has been related to the contact wire through a relation if Variant == "Bæreline" then return "Bl."..code elseif Variant == "Hengetråd" then return "Ht."..code elseif Variant == "Y-line" then return "Yl."..code elseif Variant == "Fixline" then return "Fl."..code elseif Variant == "Z-line" then return "Zl."..code elseif Variant == "Bardun" then return "Bar."..code elseif Variant == "Strever" then return "Str."..code else return _error,"Bad contact wire support Variant ["..Variant.."]." end end

LuaFunction.Description: Obtains the 'Model3DName' for this KL mast.
LuaFunction.Formula: function _EH_MAS_KlMast_Model3DName() if Variant:match("Bjelkemast") then return "NO-BN-3D-EH-MAS-BJELKEMAST-" ..OcsMastProfile .."-" ..OcsMastheight elseif Variant:match("GMB-mast") then --TODO: Få ekte data for GMB-mastene return "NO-BN-3D-EH-MAS-GMBMAST-" ..OcsMastProfile .."-" ..OcsMastheight --TODO: Lage 3D GMB-master elseif Variant:match("H-mast") then return "NO-BN-3D-EH-MAS-GITTERMAST-" ..OcsMastProfile .."-" ..OcsMastheight elseif Variant:match("B-mast") then return "NO-BN-3D-EH-MAS-GITTERMAST-" ..OcsMastProfile .."-" ..OcsMastheight elseif Variant:match("Betongmast") then return "NO-BN-3D-EH-MAS-BETONGMAST-" ..OcsMastProfile .."-" ..OcsMastheight elseif Variant:match("Tremast") then return "NO-BN-3D-EH-MAS-TREMAST-" ..OcsMastProfile .."-" ..OcsMastheight else return "Ukjent Variant ["..Variant.."]",_warning end end

LuaFunction.Name: _EH_MAS_tunnel_suspension_mast_RelativeElevation()
LuaFunction.Description: Returns the relative elevation for a ocs mast suspended from a yoke, based on the yoke's type and relative elevation.
LuaFunction.Formula: function _EH_MAS_tunnel_suspension_mast_RelativeElevation() s = "Har kl-fundament" r,n = RC__getCollectionOfRelatedObjects(s) if n == 0 then -- Belongs to a bridge underside (with no bolt group/foundation object), or has not (yet) received its bolt group relation: return 7.0,_info( "UNFINISHED - Relate mast with 'Har kl-fundament' to OCS ceiling bolt group, or delete formula and replace by actual relative height if bolt group is irrelevant.") else -- Has bolt group: return r[0].RelativeElevation,_info("Value obtained from foundation '"..RC__identify(r[0]).."'.") end end

LuaFunction.Name: _EH_MAS_tunnel_mast_Model3dName()
LuaFunction.Description: Obtains the 'Model3DName' for this OCS suspension mast.
LuaFunction.Formula: function _EH_MAS_tunnel_mast_Model3dName() if Variant:match("Hengemast i tunnel") ~= nil then if (OcsMastProfile == "Sirkulær, Ø120") then return "NO-BN-3D-EH-MAS-HENGEMAST-I-TUNNEL-SIRKULÆR-Ø120" elseif (OcsMastProfile == "Kvadratisk, 100x100") then return "NO-BN-3D-EH-MAS-HENGEMAST-I-TUNNEL-REKTANGULÆR-100x100" elseif (OcsMastProfile == "Rektangulær, 150x100") then return "NO-BN-3D-EH-MAS-HENGEMAST-I-TUNNEL-REKTANGULÆR-150x100" elseif (OcsMastProfile == "Rektangulær, 200x100") then return "NO-BN-3D-EH-MAS-HENGEMAST-I-TUNNEL-REKTANGULÆR-200x100" end elseif Variant:match("Hengemast Cariboni") ~= nil then if (OcsMastProfile == "Kvadratisk, 100x100") then return "NO-BN-3D-EH-MAS-HENGEMAST-I-TUNNEL-REKTANGULÆR-100x100" elseif (OcsMastProfile == "Rektangulær, 150x100") then return "NO-BN-3D-EH-MAS-HENGEMAST-I-TUNNEL-REKTANGULÆR-150x100" end else return "Bad OCS suspension mast Variant ["..Variant.."].",_warning end end

LuaFunction.Name: _EH_MAS_yoke_suspension_mast_code()
LuaFunction.Description: Obtains the code for this OCS suspension mast.
LuaFunction.Formula:
function _EH_MAS_yoke_suspension_mast_code() local yokeRelation = "Er hengemast i åk" local yokes, nYokes = RC__getCollectionOfRelatedObjects(yokeRelation) if nYokes == 0 then return "UNFINISHED - Relate with '"..yokeRelation.."'." elseif nYokes > 1 then return _warning,"UNFINISHED - Suspended OCS mast belongs to more than one yoke " .." - remove unintended relations '"..yokeRelation.."' or adjust the active stage using layer names." else --One yoke: local supportMastRelation = "Er åk holdt oppe av kl-mast" local supportMasts, nSupportMasts = RC__getCollectionOfRelatedObjects(supportMastRelation,yokes[0]) if nSupportMasts == 0 then return "UNFINISHED - Cannot deduce suspended OCS mast name since yoke '"..RC__identify(yokes[0]).."' has no support mast yet." else --Find the reference support mast - being closest to the yoke's own insertion point (there may be many yoke support masts): local i local shortestDist = math.huge local referenceSupportMast = nil for i = 0,nSupportMasts-1 do local newDist = RC__getDistance2D(yokes[0].geoCoord,supportMasts[i].geoCoord) if newDist < shortestDist then shortestDist = newDist referenceSupportMast = i end end
--Start suspended mast's code with support mast's code: local suspendedMastCode = supportMasts[referenceSupportMast].code
--Assign sequence number to this suspended OCS mast (counted from the support mast closest to yoke's insertion point): local suspendedMastRelation = "Er åk for hengemast_i_åk" local suspendedMasts, nSuspendedMasts = RC__getCollectionOfRelatedObjects(suspendedMastRelation,yokes[0])
local sequenceNumber = 1 local myDistance = RC__getDistance2D(supportMasts[referenceSupportMast].geoCoord,this.geoCoord) for i = 0,nSuspendedMasts-1 do local otherDistance = RC__getDistance2D(supportMasts[referenceSupportMast].geoCoord,suspendedMasts[i].geoCoord) if (suspendedMasts[i].id ~= this.id) then if otherDistance < myDistance then sequenceNumber = sequenceNumber + 1 end end end return supportMasts[referenceSupportMast].code..string.format("-%02d",sequenceNumber), _info("Code deduced from yoke '"..yokes[0].code.."' and its related components.") end end end

LuaFunction.Name: _EH_MAS_yoke_suspension_mast_Mileage()
LuaFunction.Description: Deduces the yoke suspension mast's mileage, based on its relation to a yoke/galley and this one's support mast(s).
LuaFunction.Formula:
function _EH_MAS_yoke_suspension_mast_Mileage() local ys = "Er hengemast i åk" local yr,yn = RC__getCollectionOfRelatedObjects(ys) if yn == 0 then return getPropertyValue("Mileage"),_info("UNFINISHED - Relate to yoke/galley with '"..ys.."' to set mileage automatically.")
elseif yn > 1 then return getPropertyValue("Mileage"), _info("ERROR - Suspension mast is related to more than one yoke ("..RC__identify(yr[0])..", "..RC__identify(yr[1])..").")
else --yn == 1
local s = "Er åk holdt oppe av kl-mast" local r,n = RC__getCollectionOfRelatedObjects(s,yr[0]) if n == 0 then return RC__getMileageFromRelatedObject(s), _info("Mileage deduced from yoke/galley lacking support mast(s) '"..RC__identify(yr[0]).."'.")
elseif n == 1 then --Galley: return RC__getMileageFromRelatedObject(s),_info("Mileage deduced from support mast '"..RC__identify(r[0]).."'.")
elseif n >= 2 then --Our mast is suspended from a yoke yr[0] being supported by OCS masts r[0] and r[1]: local m1 = r[0] local m2 = r[1] -- Not needed: if RC__getDistance2D(this,m1) > RC__getDistance2D(this,m2) then m1,m2 = m2,m1 end local x1 = m1.geoCoord.X local y1 = m1.geoCoord.Y local dx = m2.geoCoord.X - x1 local dy = m2.geoCoord.Y - y1
--Find point Q on the straight line betweeen m1 and m2 with the yoke suspension mast's specified DistanceToAlignment: function err(t) local Qx = x1+t*dx local Qy = y1+t*dy return getAlignmentInfo(Alignment.id,Qx,Qy).DistanceToAlignment - this.DistanceToAlignment end local tq = getZeros(err,{tolerance = 1e-4, interval = {0,1}, timeLimit = 3})[0] local Qx = x1 + tq*dx local Qy = y1 + tq*dy return getAlignmentInfo(Alignment.id,Qx,Qy).Mileage end end end

LuaFunction.Name: _EH_MAS_yoke_suspension_mast_RelativeElevation()
LuaFunction.Description: Returns the relative elevation for a ocs mast suspended from a yoke, based on the yoke's type and relative elevation.
LuaFunction.Formula: function _EH_MAS_yoke_suspension_mast_RelativeElevation() local s,r,n,e,v s = "Er hengemast i åk" r,n = RC__getCollectionOfRelatedObjects(s) if n == 0 then return 0.0,_info("UNFINISHED - Relate with 'Er hengemast i åk' to its OCS yoke.") else e = (r[0].geoCoord.Z - getAlignmentInfo().Elevation) + 0.10 --Above bottom of yoke v = r[0].Variant if v:match("12") then return e + 0.8 elseif v:match("14") then return e + 1.2 elseif v:match("40") then return e + 0.4 else return 0.0,_error,_info("Bad related OCS yoke '"..RC__identify(r[0]).."' Variant: ["..v.."].") end end end

LuaFunction.Name: _EH_MAS_chkTriggerRelatedObjects()
LuaFunction.Description: Triggers modelchecking in the yoke's masts.
LuaFunction.Formula: function _EH_MAS_chkTriggerRelatedObjects() local yokeRelation = "Er hengemast i åk" local yokes, nYokes = RC__getCollectionOfRelatedObjects(yokeRelation) if nYokes == 0 then return 0,_info("UNFINISHED - Relate with '"..yokeRelation.."'.") elseif nYokes >= 1 then local t = {} local i local s1 = "Er åk holdt oppe av kl-mast" local r1,n1 = RC__getCollectionOfRelatedObjects(s1,yokes[0]) for i = 0,n1-1 do table.insert(t,r1[i]) end s2 = "Er åk for hengemast_i_åk" local r2,n2 = RC__getCollectionOfRelatedObjects(s2,yokes[0]) for i = 0,n2-1 do table.insert(t,r2[i]) end --if true then return nYokes,yokes,n1,r1,n2,r2 end return n1+n2,t,_info(n1+n2.." masts have been refreshed.") end end

LuaFunction.Name: _EH_AAK_DistanceToAlignment()
LuaFunction.Description: Returns the distance to alignment for the yoke.
LuaFunction.Formula:
function _EH_AAK_DistanceToAlignment() -- Ref Bane NOR, lærebok "Bygging av kontaktledningsanlegg" Del 2:2, Kap. 14
function _EH_AAK_get_mastDistanceToAlignment(mast) if mast.Alignment == nil then return RightSided and 4e-4 or -4e-4,_warning,_info("Closest OCS support mast is not connected to a track (own alignment).") else local mv = mast.Variant local mp = mast.OcsMastProfile local d if mv:match("Bjelkemast") ~= nil then d = string.sub(mp,4,6)/2000 --Assume mast profile names "HEB200", "HEB220" etc elseif mv:match("GMB-mast") ~= nil then d = string.sub(mp,4,6)/2000 --Assume mast profile names "HEB200", "HEB220" etc TODO: Finn ekte profiler for GMB-mast elseif mv:match("B-mast") ~= nil then d = (mast.OcsMastheight - RelativeElevation) * math.tan(23/1000000) elseif mv:match("H-mast") ~= nil then d = (mast.OcsMastheight - RelativeElevation) * math.tan(1/50000) elseif mv:match("Hengemast") ~= nil then if (mp == 'Sirkulær, Ø120') then d = 0.06 elseif (mp == 'Kvadratisk, 100x100') then d = 0.05 elseif (mp == 'Rektangulær, 150x100') then d = 0.075 elseif (mp == 'Rektangulær, 200x100') then d = 0.1 else return 0,_warning,_info("Bad OCS mast profile ["..mp.."].") end else return 0,_warning,_info("Bad OCS mast variant ["..mv.."].") end -- OCS mast and yoke may belong to different tracks (when OCS mast is located between tracks): mdist = getAlignmentInfo(alignment.id,mast.geoCoord.X,mast.geoCoord.Y).DistanceToAlignment --Distance from center closest OCS mast to yoke's alignment if (mast.RightSided) then if (mast.Alignment.id == Alignment.id) then return mdist-d else return mdist+d end else if (mast.Alignment.id == Alignment.id) then return mdist+d else return mdist-d end end end end --function
local RelationName = "Er åk holdt oppe av kl-mast" local r,n = RC__getCollectionOfRelatedObjects(RelationName) if n == 0 then if Variant == "Utliggeråk" then return getPropertyValue("DistanceToAlignment"),_warning,_info("UNFINISHED: Relate galley to an OCS mast with relation '"..RelationName.."'.") else return getPropertyValue("DistanceToAlignment"),_warning,_info( "UNFINISHED: Relate yoke to OCS mast(s) with relation '"..RelationName.."', or change Variant to galley (Utliggeråk).") end
elseif n == 1 then if Variant == "Utliggeråk" then return _EH_AAK_get_mastDistanceToAlignment(r[0]),_info("Galley yoke (Utliggeråk) extending from mast '"..RC__identify(r[0]).."'.") else return getPropertyValue("DistanceToAlignment"),_warning,_info( "UNFINISHED: Relate yoke to one more OCS mast with relation 'Har åk-mast / kl-mast', or change Variant to galley (Utliggeråk).") end
elseif n >= 2 then local m1 = r[0] local m2 = r[1] if RC__getDistance2D(this,m1) > RC__getDistance2D(this,m2) then m1,m2 = m2,m1 end local d1 = RC__getDistance2D(m1,m2) local L = math.floor(1.500 + d1) --Assume min 0.5 and max 1.5 meter total yoke length overshoot local d2 = 0.5 * (L - d1) --Share overshoot between masts local x1 = m1.geoCoord.X local y1 = m1.geoCoord.Y local x2 = m2.geoCoord.X local y2 = m2.geoCoord.Y local x = x1 - (d2/d1)*(x2-x1) local y = y1 - (d2/d1)*(y2-y1) local info = "Distance to alignment deduced through support mast '"..RC__identify(m1).."' related by '"..RelationName.."'." return getAlignmentInfo(Alignment.id,x,y).DistanceToAlignment,_info(info) end end

LuaFunction.Name: _EH_AAK_Length()
LuaFunction.Description: Returns the length of the yoke, being the mast-mast center distance plus 1.50 meter, rounded down.
LuaFunction.Formula:
function _EH_AAK_Length() -- Ref Bane NOR, lærebok "Bygging av kontaktledningsanlegg" Del 2:2, Kap. 14 local RelationName = "Er åk holdt oppe av kl-mast" local r,n = RC__getCollectionOfRelatedObjects(RelationName) local L if n == 0 then if Variant == "Utliggeråk" then L = "6m" return L,_warning,_info("UNFINISHED: Relate galley to an OCS mast with relation '"..RelationName.."'.") else if Variant == "Type 12" then L = "11m" elseif Variant == "Type 14" then L = "28m" elseif Variant == "Type 40" then L = "10m" end return L,_warning,_info( "UNFINISHED: Relate yoke to OCS mast(s) with relation '"..RelationName.."', or change Variant to galley (Utliggeråk).") end
elseif n == 1 then local m1 = r[0] if Variant == "Utliggeråk" then return "6m",_info("Galley yoke (Utliggeråk) extending from mast "..m1.code..".") else if Variant == "Type 12" then L = "11m" elseif Variant == "Type 14" then L = "28m" elseif Variant == "Type 40" then L = "10m" end return L,_warning,_info( "UNFINISHED: Relate yoke to one more OCS mast with relation 'Har åk-mast / kl-mast', or change Variant to galley (Utliggeråk).") end
elseif n >= 2 then local m1 = r[0] local m2 = r[1] local P1 = m1.geoCoord local P2 = m2.geoCoord local len = RC__getDistance2D(P1,P2) L = math.floor(len + 1.5) if Variant == "Type 12" then if L < 11 then return "11m",_warning,_info("L="..L.." required, but Type 12 yokes can't be shorter than 11 meter. Change to type 40 or galley (Utliggeråk).") elseif L > 33 then return "33m",_warning,_info("L="..L.." required, but Type 12 yokes can't be longer than 33 meter, change to Type 14.") end elseif Variant == "Type 14" then if L < 28 then return "28m",_warning,_info("L="..L.." required, but Type 14 yokes can't be made shorter than 28 meter. Change to Type 12 or 40.") elseif L > 43 then return "43m",_warning,_info("L="..L.." required, but Type 14 yokes can't be made longer than 43 meter.") end elseif Variant == "Type 40" then if L < 10 then return "10m",_warning,_info("L="..L.." required, but Type 40 yokes can't be made shorter than 10 meter. Change to galley (Utliggeråk).") elseif L > 16 then return "16m",_warning,_info("L="..L.." required, but Type 40 yokes can't be made longer than 16 meter, change to Type 12 or 14.") end else return getPropertyValue("Length"),_error,_info("Remove excess yoke support mast(s), or change yoke Variant into Type 12/14/40.") end return L.."m",_info("Length deduced from mast "..m1.code.." and "..m2.code.." ("..RC__round(len,3).." m).") end end

CustomAttribute.Name: SubVariant
CustomAttribute.Description: The cantilever subvariant [Standard | Redusert] is 'Standard' when built for its line design speed, and 'Redusert' when built for less tense wires and lesser speeds.

CustomAttribute.Name: PushDirection
CustomAttribute.Description: The cantilever push direction (cpd) [Strekk | Trykk] is denoted 'Strekk' if the cantilever pulls the contact wire towards the cantilever console(s), and 'Trykk' if it pushes it away.

CustomAttribute.Name: ContactWireHeight
CustomAttribute.Description: The contact wire height (cwh) [m] denotes the orthogonal distance from the plane formed by the top-of-rails to the contact wire clamp.

CustomAttribute.Name: SystemHeight
CustomAttribute.Description: The cantilever system height (sh) [m] denotes the vertical Z coordinate difference from the contact wire clamp to the catenary clamp.

CustomAttribute.Name: WireClampOffset
CustomAttribute.Description: The wire clamp offset (wco) [m] denotes the distance to a sideways neutral clamp posision. The wco is positive for offsets to the right side of the alignment in the direction of increasing mileage.

CustomAttribute.Name: CatenaryClampOffset
CustomAttribute.Description: The catenary clamp offset (cco) [m] denotes the distance to a sideways neutral clamp posision. The cco is positive for offsets to the right side of the alignment in the direction of increasing mileage.

CustomAttribute.Name: StitchWireLength
CustomAttribute.Description: The stitch wire length (swl) [m] denotes the length, measured as a difference in mileage, from start to end (where it attaches to the catenary wire). Zero length means 'no stitch wire'.

CustomAttribute.Name: Stagger
CustomAttribute.Description: Stagger [m] denotes the distance from contact wire clamp to centre track, measured co-linearly with the top-of-rails plane. Positive stagger means pushing away from mast, negative means pulling towards mast.

CustomAttribute.Name: StaggerDisplay
CustomAttribute.Description: The stagger value, as shown next to the cantilever [cm].

CustomAttribute.Name: AddVisual2dAngularOffset
CustomAttribute.Description: The 'AddVisual2dAngularOffset' [Double] adds 16.7 decimal degrees to the 2D symbol's angle. Cantilevers mounted in a yoke or galley will not be visible unless the 2D symbol is given an extra angle.

CustomAttribute.Name: mc_OcsSystemHeight
CustomAttribute.Description: Check that cantilever system height (sh) [m] conforms to Technical Regulations for the chosen Variant / SubVariant.

LuaFunction.Name: _EH_UTL_code()
LuaFunction.Description: Obtains the 'code' for this OCS cantilever. Uses relation 'Tilhører kl-mast' to access the related object's data.
LuaFunction.Formula: function _EH_UTL_code() s = "Tilhører kl-mast/hengemast_i_åk" r,n = RC__getCollectionOfRelatedObjects(s) if n == 0 then return "UNFINISHED - Relate with 'Tilhører kl-mast/hengemast_i_åk' to an OCS mast." else return r[0].code,_info("Cantilever belongs to mast "..RC__identify(r[0])) end end

LuaFunction.Name: _EH_UTL_chkSystemHeight()
LuaFunction.Description: Checks the cantilever's height as a function of selected OCS system variant's min and max heights.
LuaFunction.Formula: function _EH_UTL_chkSystemHeight() min = _EH_UTL_StandardValues(Variant)["shmin"] max = _EH_UTL_StandardValues(Variant)["shmax"] sh = SystemHeight v = Variant if sh < min then return string.format("%.02f: WARNING - system height is below %s limit (%.02f).",sh,v,min),_warning elseif sh > max then return string.format("%.02f: WARNING - system height is above %s limit (%.02f).",sh,v,max),_warning else return string.format("%.02f: OK - system height is within %s limits [%.02f-%0.2f].",sh,v,min,max),_ok end end

LuaFunction.Formula: function _EH_KLK_DistanceToAlignment() s = "Tilhører utligger" r,n = RC__getCollectionOfRelatedObjects(s) if n == 0 then return 0,_info("UNFINISHED - Relate with '"..s.."' to a cantilever.") else cwh = r[0].ContactWireHeight zigzag = r[0].Stagger if Alignment == nil then return 0,_warning,_info("UNFINISHED - own alignment must be assigned.") end ai = getAlignmentInfo() if not ai.NormalProjectionExists then return 0,_warning,_info("UNFINISHED - object is misplaced wrt own alignment.") end h = ai.Cant -- The track's superelevation in millimeters cr = ai.CantRotation -- CW or CCW return 0,_info("TODO: Lua code for this property is not yet ready for use.") end end

LuaFunction.Name: _FE_DIV_ocs_annotation_name()
LuaFunction.Description: Obtains the 'name' for a OCS annotation item.
LuaFunction.Formula: function _FE_DIV_ocs_annotation_name() local RelationName = "Er KL-annotering for anything" local r,n = RC__getCollectionOfRelatedObjects(RelationName) if Variant:match("felt") then if n == 0 then return "UNFINISHED - Relate OCS contact wire change annotation to its two catenary wire alignments with '" ..RelationName.."'." elseif n == 1 then return "UNFINISHED - Relate OCS contact wire change annotation for contact wire '" ..r[0].code.."' to one more catenary wire alignment with '"..RelationName.."'." elseif n == 2 then -- NB! The user should use the ManageProperties Relations tab and just drag-and-drop relations in -- the datagrid to modify the sequence of relations (which modifies the text shown in modelspace). local a = r[0] local b = r[1] if (Variant == "Vekslingsfelt annotering") then return "VEKSLINGSFELT".." L"..a.code.." / L"..b.code elseif (Variant == "Seksjonsfelt annotering") then return "SEKSJONSFELT".." L"..a.code.." / L"..b.code elseif (Variant == "Sugefelt annotering") then return "SUGEFELT".." L"..a.code.." / L"..b.code end else return _warning,"Too many ["..n.."] related items - relate OCS contact wire change annotation to exactly two catenary wire alignments with '" ..RelationName.."', or adjust stage settings using layer names." end elseif Variant:match("Fritekst") then if code ~= nil and code ~= "" then return code else if n == 0 then return "UNFINISHED - Relate OCS annotation with variant '"..Variant.."' to its items with '" ..RelationName.."' and define the 'code' or 'name' property." else local s,i s = RC__identify(r[0]) for i = 1, n-1 do s = s..", "..RC__identify(r[i]) end return "UNFINISHED - Define the 'code' property or change the 'name' property to annotate related items ["..s.."]." end end else return _error,"Bad variant ["..Variant.."] - cannot annotate items" end end

LuaFunction.Name: _EH_AEH_dir()
LuaFunction.Description: Obtains the 'dir' for this OCS tensioning device, related to its alignment's direction.
LuaFunction.Formula: function _EH_AEH_dir() if Alignment == nil then return "unknown",_info("UNFINISHED: Own Alignment (contact wire) undefined for OCS tensioning device.") else return RC__getDistance2D(Alignment.RcAlignment.StartPoint) < RC__getDistance2D(Alignment.RcAlignment.EndPoint) and "up" or "down" end end

LuaFunction.Name: _EH_AEH_code()
LuaFunction.Description: Obtains the 'code' for this OCS tensioning device, related to its wire with 'Avspenner kontaktledning'.
LuaFunction.Formula: function _EH_AEH_code() if Alignment == nil then return _warning,"UNFINISHED: Own Alignment (contact wire) undefined for OCS tensioning device." else if Variant:lower():match("fix") then local RelationName = "Avspenner kontaktledning" local r,n = RC__getCollectionOfRelatedObjects(RelationName) if n == 0 then return "UNFINISHED - Relate fixpoint tensioning device with its catenary wire alignments with '" ..RelationName.."'." else return r[0].code end else return Alignment.code end end end

LuaFunction.Name: _EH_AEH_name()
LuaFunction.Description: Obtains the 'name' for this OCS tensioning device, related to its wire with 'Avspenner kontaktledning'.
LuaFunction.Formula: function _EH_AEH_name() if Variant:match("Fix") then return "L"..code .. " - [FIX]" elseif Variant:match("Fjær") then return "L"..code .. " - [FJ]" elseif Variant:match("Fast") then return "L"..code .. " - [F]" elseif Variant:match("Lodd") then return "L"..code .. " - [L]" else return "Unknown tensioning device variant ["..Variant.."].",_warning end end

LuaFunction.Name: _EH_AEH_Model3dName()
LuaFunction.Description: Obtains the 3D Model Name for this OCS tensioning device.
LuaFunction.Formula: function _EH_AEH_Model3dName() t = "NO-BN-3D-EH-AEH-AVSPENNING" if Variant:match("Fix") then return t.."-FIXPUNKT" else if Variant:match("Fjær") then t = t.."-FJÆR" elseif Variant:match("Fast") then t = t.."-FAST" elseif Variant:match("Lodd") then t = t.."-LODD" end if Variant:match("enkel") then return t.."-ENKEL" elseif Variant:match("dobbel") then return t.."-DOBBEL" end end return _info("Bad tensioning device variant ["..Variant.."].") end

LuaFunction.Name: _EH_AEH_TensileForces()
LuaFunction.Description: Obtains the tensile forces for this OCS tensioning device, of OcsSystem type The OCS System is one of [Unknown | S20A | S20AR (redusert) | S20B | S20BR | S20C1 | S20C2 | S25 | S35 | S35MS | Cariboni].
LuaFunction.Formula: function _EH_AEH_TensileForces(os) tf = NOBN_ocs_getTensioningStandardValues(os) if os == "Unknown" then return "?/? kN (UNFINISHED - unknown OcsSystem)" elseif Variant:match("Fix") then return tf.awtf.." kN (fix)" else if Variant:match("Fjær") or Variant:match("Fast") or Variant:match("Lodd") then return tf.cwtf.."/"..tf.catf.." kN" end end return _info("Bad tensioning device variant ["..Variant.."].") end

LuaFunction.Name: _SA_SSP_DistanceToAlignment()
LuaFunction.Description: Returns the XY plane distance to alignment for a derailer or catch points (cant taken into consideration).

LuaFunction.Name: _SA_SSP_Model3dName()
LuaFunction.Description: Returns the 3D model name for a derailer object (we have no catch points in 3D yet).
LuaFunction.Formula: function _SA_SSP_Model3dName() --Ignore the DerailerState property - always draw in the derailing state. local t = "NO-BN-3D-SA-SSP" if Variant:upper():match("ENKEL") then t = t.."-ENKEL" elseif Variant:upper():match("DOBBEL") then t = t.."-DOBBEL" else t = t.."-BAD_VARIANT" end if derailSide == 'left' then t = t.."-VSIDE" elseif derailSide == 'right' then t = t.."-HSIDE" else t = t.."-BAD_DERAILSIDE" end return t end

LuaFunction.Name: NOBN_sig_chkTriggerNeighbourAxleCounters()
LuaFunction.Description: Triggers modelchecking in neighbour axle counters.
LuaFunction.Formula: function NOBN_sig_chkTriggerNeighbourAxleCounters() if Alignment == nil then return "UNFINISHED - Missing own alignment.",_error end local n = 0 local t = {} prevAc = getDownObject("SA-TEL Tellepunkt") --Axle counter if prevAc ~= nil then n = n + 1 table.insert(t,prevAc) end nextAc = getUpObject("SA-TEL Tellepunkt") --Axle counter if nextAc ~= nil then n = n + 1 table.insert(t,nextAc) end return n,t,_info(n.." axle counters have been refreshed.") end

LuaFunction.Name: NOBN_sig_chkCableDistanceFromTunerToAxleCounter()
LuaFunction.Description: Checks 'grid distance' (from track + along track), from axle counter tuner (mushroom) to its axle counter. Error if outside (1.0 - 7.5), warning if outside (3.0 - 3.4) meter.
LuaFunction.Formula: function NOBN_sig_chkCableDistanceFromTunerToAxleCounter() --Assume mushroom has same own alignment and approximate position as the axle counter it belongs to: s = "Er akseltellersopp for tellepunkt" r,n = RC__getCollectionOfRelatedObjects(s) if n == 0 then return "UNFINISHED - Relate with '"..s.."' to its axle counter sensor." else tol = RC__EPSILON() * 1.0 -- meter ac = r[0] gridDistancePerpendicular = math.abs(distanceToAlignment - ac.distanceToAlignment) gridDistanceColinear = math.abs(mileage - ac.mileage) -- Their sum is a cool metric: gridDistance = gridDistancePerpendicular + gridDistanceColinear msg = "Grid distance is the sum of "..RC__round(gridDistancePerpendicular,1).." (perpendicular to alignment) and "..RC__round(gridDistanceColinear,1).." (colinear to alignment)" gt = string.format("%.1f=%.03f+%.03f",gridDistance,gridDistancePerpendicular,gridDistanceColinear) if (gridDistance < tol) then return gridDistance..": ERROR - Tuner is located too close to axle counter wrt minimum tolerance 1m.",{ac},_error,_info(msg) elseif (gridDistance >= 1.0 and gridDistance < 3.0) then return gt..": WARNING - Tuner is located close to axle counter but above min 1m - try increase to 3.0.",{ac},_warning,_info(msg) elseif (gridDistance >= 3.0 and gridDistance < 3.4) then return gt..": OK - Distance from tuner to axle counter is suitable for standard cabling 3m to 3.4m.",{ac},_ok,_info(msg) elseif (gridDistance >= 3.4 and gridDistance <= 7.5) then return gt..": WARNING - Tuner is located far from axle counter, but below max 7.5m - try reduce to 3.4.",{ac},_warning,_info(msg) else return gt..": ERROR - Tuner is located too far from axle counter, reduce distance.",{ac},_error,_info(msg) end end end

LuaFunction.Name: _SA_TPS_code()
LuaFunction.Description: Obtains the 'code' for axle counter tuning unit (mushroom). Uses relation 'Er akseltellersopp for tellepunkt' to , the related object's data.
LuaFunction.Formula: function _SA_TPS_code() s = "Er akseltellersopp for tellepunkt" r,n = RC__getCollectionOfRelatedObjects(s) if n == 0 then return "UNFINISHED - Relate with '"..s.."' to its axle counter sensor." else return r[0].code end end

LuaFunction.Name: _SA_DRV_code()
LuaFunction.Description: Obtains the code for a point machine, derived from the switch it is related to with 'Driver sporveksel'.
LuaFunction.Formula: function _SA_DRV_code() local s,i,sw,n,d,j s = "Driver sporveksel" sw,n = RC__getCollectionOfRelatedObjects(s) if n == 0 then return "Relate with '"..s.."' to switch object (turnout).", _info("Point machines derive their code from the switch they are related to with '"..s.."'.") else pm,npm = RC__getCollectionOfRelatedObjects("Har sporvekseldrivmaskin",sw[0]) j = 0 for i = 0, npm-1 do d = (sw[0].dir == "up") and 1 or -1 if ((ReferenceMileage - pm[i].ReferenceMileage)*d >= 0) then j = j + 1 end end return sw[0].code.."_"..j end end

LuaFunction.Name: _SA_DRV_dir()
LuaFunction.Description: Obtains the direction (dir) for a point machine, derived from the switch it is related to with 'Driver sporveksel'.
LuaFunction.Formula: function _SA_DRV_dir() local s,sw,n s = "Driver sporveksel" sw,n = RC__getCollectionOfRelatedObjects(s) if n == 0 then return "unknown",_info("Point machines derive their direction from the switch they are related to with '"..s.."'.") else return sw[0].dir end end

LuaFunction.Name: _SA_DRV_Model3DName()
LuaFunction.Description: Obtains the 3D model name (Model3DName) for a point machine, derived from its Variant, direction (dir) and side of alignment (distanceToAlignment).
LuaFunction.Formula: function _SA_DRV_Model3DName() local t if Variant == "Alstom MET" then t = "NO-BN-3D-SA-DRV-ALSTOM-MET-KASSESVILLE-" elseif Variant == "Siemens Bsg9" then t = "NO-BN-3D-SA-DRV-SIEMENS-BSG9-" elseif Variant == "Siemens ELS 710" then t = "NO-BN-3D-SA-DRV-SIEMENS-ELS710-" else return "NO-BN-3D-UKJENT",_error,_info("Bad Variant ["..Variant.."].") end if ((dir == "up" and RightSided) or (dir == "down" and LeftSided)) then return t.."HSIDE" elseif ((dir == "up" and LeftSided) or (dir == "down" and RightSided)) then return t.."VSIDE" else return "Cannot determine side of track for point machine.",_error end end

LuaFunction.Name: _SA_LOK_code()
LuaFunction.Description: Obtains the code for a local control panel, derived from the switch or derailer it is related to with 'Driver sporveksel' or 'Driver sporsperre'.
LuaFunction.Formula: function _SA_LOK_code() s = "Omstiller sporveksel/sporsperre" r,n = RC__getCollectionOfRelatedObjects(s) if n == 0 then return "UNFINISHED - Missing relation '"..s.."' to switch object or derailer object.",_warning, _info("A local control panel derives its code property from the switch or derailer which it is related to.") elseif n == 1 then if r[0].RcType == "KO-SPV Sporveksel" then coupledSwitch,ncsw = RC__getCollectionOfRelatedObjects("Er koblet med sporveksel",sw[0]) if ncsw == 0 then return r[0].code else return coupledSwitch[0].code.."/"..r[0].code end elseif r[0].RcType == "SA-SSP Sporsperre" then return r[0].code else return "ERROR - Bad RcType ["..r[0].RcType.."] for object related to Local control panel.",_error end else return "ERROR - More than 1 ["..n.."] object related to Local control panel.",_error end end

CustomAttribute.Name: mc_DistanceToNextBalise
CustomAttribute.Description:
Below 2.35 meter: ERROR - Balise magnetic fields may merge - increase distance
 2.35-2.8 meter: WARNING - Outside recommended tolerance - increase distance
 2.8-3.2 meter: OK - The train will treat the balises as in the same group
 3.2-3.5 meter: WARNING - Outside recommended tolerance - decrease distance
 3.5-10.5 meter: ERROR - The train cannot determine balise group assignment
 10.5-11.8 meter: WARNING - Outside recommended tolerance - Increase distance
 Above 11.8 meter: OK - The train will treat the balises as belonging to different groups

CustomAttribute.Name: mc_DistanceToPreviousBalise
CustomAttribute.Description:
Below 2.35 meter: ERROR - Balise magnetic fields may merge - increase distance
 2.35-2.8 meter: WARNING - Outside recommended tolerance - increase distance
 2.8-3.2 meter: OK - The train will treat the balises as in the same group
 3.2-3.5 meter: WARNING - Outside recommended tolerance - decrease distance
 3.5-10.5 meter: ERROR - The train cannot determine balise group assignment
 10.5-11.8 meter: WARNING - Outside recommended tolerance - Increase distance
 Above 11.8 meter: OK - The train will treat the balises as belonging to different groups

CustomAttribute.Name: mc_DistanceToTrackVertically
CustomAttribute.Description: Below 2 meter: ERROR – Balise may be read by a train in the neighbouring track – increase distance\n 2-2.6 meter: WARNING – Allowed on condition that at least one of the group's A- and B-balise is above 2.6 meter from neighbouring track (large balise) resp. 2.3 meter (minibalise) – increase distance\n Over 2.6 meter: OK – Train in neighbouring track will pass without reading the balise

CustomAttribute.Name: mc_DistanceToTrackSideways
CustomAttribute.Description: Below 2 meter: ERROR – Balise may be read by a train in the neighbouring track – increase distance\n 2-2.6 meter: WARNING – Allowed on condition that at least one of the group's A- and B-balise is above 2.6 meter from neighbouring track (large balise) resp. 2.3 meter (minibalise) – increase distance\n Over 2.6 meter: OK – Train in neighbouring track will pass without reading the balise
